(Intelligent Document Assistant Sample) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This sample document describes a production-style retrieval augmented generation system.) Tj
T*
(The application lets users upload PDF files, extracts text, cleans the content, and splits the text into overlapping semantic chunks.) Tj
T*
(Each chunk is embedded and stored in a persistent ChromaDB vector database so future documents can be added without rebuilding the whole index.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When a user asks a question, the system retrieves the most relevant chunks, sends those chunks to the language model as context, and instructs the model to answer only from the uploaded documents.) Tj
T*
(The interface displays source file names, page numbers, chunk text, retrieval scores, response time, and retrieval latency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The evaluation layer measures answer relevance, context relevance, faithfulness, hallucination risk, retrieval quality, and latency.) Tj
T*
(These metrics are saved to local history and displayed in a dashboard so engineers can monitor RAG quality over time.) Tj
T*
